{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory suicide risk assessment for adolescents in hospital who express intent",
        "additional_details": "I want the Government to make suicide risk assessments legally mandatory when a child expresses intent to harm themselves. I am concerned that current guidance is inconsistent and not always enforced. No child who asks for help should be left without a full assessment, protection, and proper support. This could be called Ella's law.",
        "background": "Make full suicide risk assessments mandatory when a child in hospital care expresses intent to harm themselves. No child asking for help should be left without support.",
